  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR satellite session at the 5th Global Symposium on Health Systems Research</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Raise the profile of NIHR in the global health research funding landscape. 2) Bring together researchers and thought-leaders to inform the development of the GHR team&#x2019;s future activities in global HSR. 3) Provide support to the participation of low- and middle-income country (LMIC)-based speakers in the Symposium.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To inform the development of a dedicated NIHR-led Health Policy and Systems Research (HPSR) programme and the co-creation of strategic partnerships addressing global HPSR, NIHR is undertaking outreach and consultation activities to establish areas where there is an unmet need or skill shortage, and areas which are under-funded or under-researched. The 5th Global HSR Symposium (a biennial event held in the UK for the first time in 2018) presented a unique opportunity for NIHR to engage in an international event and consult stakeholders through the organisation of a dedicated satellite session.</narrative>
  </description>
